01:02:40.620 --> 01:02:42.650
but I saw before.

01:02:42.650 --> 01:02:49.640
So if I create a progressing
wave in a single--

01:02:49.640 --> 01:02:56.540
in a closed end, open end
tube, this progressing wave

01:02:56.540 --> 01:03:00.068
is going to be propagating
at the speed of what?

01:03:00.068 --> 01:03:01.490
The speed of what?

01:03:01.490 --> 01:03:02.170
AUDIENCE: Sound.

01:03:02.170 --> 01:03:03.170
YEN-JIE LEE: Sound, yes.

01:03:03.170 --> 01:03:06.380
It's going to be propagating
at the speed of sound,

01:03:06.380 --> 01:03:08.525
and you would
reach the boundary.

01:03:11.880 --> 01:03:16.356
The question is,
will we see this?

01:03:16.356 --> 01:03:23.880
Would this progressing wave just
simply leak out of the tube.

01:03:26.910 --> 01:03:28.965
How many of you think
that's going to happen?

01:03:31.700 --> 01:03:35.330
I hope I will never see
that again in the exam.

01:03:35.330 --> 01:03:36.415
This would never happen.

01:03:39.050 --> 01:03:40.620
Why?

01:03:40.620 --> 01:03:49.370
That means you will have a super
narrow collimated progressing

01:03:49.370 --> 01:03:52.370
wave going straight
out of a tube,

01:03:52.370 --> 01:03:58.110
and that will not actually
match the boundary conditions

01:03:58.110 --> 01:04:00.500
at the end of the tube.

01:04:00.500 --> 01:04:03.740
So that means,
basically, first of all,

01:04:03.740 --> 01:04:08.190
there was no refraction.

01:04:08.190 --> 01:04:12.470
That means that all the
energy is transferred

01:04:12.470 --> 01:04:14.370
outside of the world.

01:04:14.370 --> 01:04:18.190
And according to what
we discussed before,

01:04:18.190 --> 01:04:21.420
what you would expect is
that, OK, now you suddenly

01:04:21.420 --> 01:04:29.040
change to environment which you
have really very large volume.

01:04:29.040 --> 01:04:33.240
Therefore, you it will be
very difficult to change

01:04:33.240 --> 01:04:36.410
the pressure
outside of the tube.

01:04:36.410 --> 01:04:38.160
Because what you are
actually connected to

01:04:38.160 --> 01:04:43.470
is a reserve of infinite
number of molecules outside.

01:04:43.470 --> 01:04:48.320
It's going to be really
hard to change the pressure.

01:04:48.320 --> 01:04:51.300
Therefore, apparently
this behavior

01:04:51.300 --> 01:04:53.850
doesn't match the
boundary condition.

01:04:53.850 --> 01:04:57.000
And therefore, what
you should expect

01:04:57.000 --> 01:05:02.530
is something like this,
which I can show you here.

01:05:02.530 --> 01:05:06.220
So in this case, you
have both side opened.

01:05:06.220 --> 01:05:10.540
What is going to happen is that
at the boundary-- actually,

01:05:10.540 --> 01:05:14.530
it's like the case
of hitting a wall,

01:05:14.530 --> 01:05:19.000
because outside of the
tube you have really,

01:05:19.000 --> 01:05:23.600
really large volume, huge
amount of air out of it.

01:05:23.600 --> 01:05:26.680
Therefore, it's
like hitting a wall.

01:05:26.680 --> 01:05:29.590
The amplitude of
the progressing wave

01:05:29.590 --> 01:05:34.030
changes sine and goes
back through the tube.

01:05:34.030 --> 01:05:37.070
And of course, this system
is actually not perfect.

01:05:37.070 --> 01:05:41.590
Therefore, there can
be some leaking out--

01:05:41.590 --> 01:05:46.390
some energy leak out of
the tube, which essentially

01:05:46.390 --> 01:05:50.320
must be happening, because
we can actually roll the tube

01:05:50.320 --> 01:05:52.000
and we can hear the sound.

01:05:52.000 --> 01:05:54.210
That is because some
of the sound wave

01:05:54.210 --> 01:05:56.110
actually leaks out of the tube.

01:05:56.110 --> 01:05:59.530
And this process will
go over and over again.

01:05:59.530 --> 01:06:02.290
And this progressing
wave is going

01:06:02.290 --> 01:06:06.850
to be going back and
forth, like that.

01:06:06.850 --> 01:06:11.730
So I hope that after this
demonstration everybody

01:06:11.730 --> 01:06:15.136
will expect that, OK,
this will be not--

01:06:15.136 --> 01:06:21.370
the result will be like
this progressing wave

01:06:21.370 --> 01:06:25.900
is going to be reflected because
of the boundary condition

01:06:25.900 --> 01:06:29.768
and also change sine
in terms of amplitude.

01:06:35.450 --> 01:06:37.280
So what we have learned today--

01:06:37.280 --> 01:06:39.930
so it's already
close to the end.

01:06:39.930 --> 01:06:46.390
We have learned example
of a longitudinal wave

01:06:46.390 --> 01:06:49.790
And basically, longitudinal
wave is actually

01:06:49.790 --> 01:06:54.140
in the form of density
wave in the example

01:06:54.140 --> 01:06:55.940
which we covered today.

01:06:55.940 --> 01:07:00.080
And the mathematical
description of the sound wave

01:07:00.080 --> 01:07:03.350
is going to be almost
identical to what

01:07:03.350 --> 01:07:09.170
we have learned from the
string case, which we actually

01:07:09.170 --> 01:07:13.370
discussed last time.

01:07:13.370 --> 01:07:15.770
There are two
boundary conditions

01:07:15.770 --> 01:07:20.330
which I would like to
briefly discuss before we

01:07:20.330 --> 01:07:23.310
end the lecture today.

01:07:23.310 --> 01:07:32.380
So in the case of open end,
as we discussed before,

01:07:32.380 --> 01:07:34.750
we can have a system
which contains

01:07:34.750 --> 01:07:40.400
a closed end and an open end.

01:07:40.400 --> 01:07:43.900
What will be the boundary
condition for a closed end?

01:07:43.900 --> 01:07:47.080
So the closed end
have a wall here.

01:07:47.080 --> 01:07:52.438
Therefore, when you
have your molecule,

01:07:52.438 --> 01:07:55.540
the air molecule
oscillating back and forth,

01:07:55.540 --> 01:08:02.590
when they are actually close to
the wall, they cannot vibrate.

01:08:02.590 --> 01:08:03.090
Why?

01:08:03.090 --> 01:08:04.790
Because it's hitting the wall.

01:08:04.790 --> 01:08:07.420
It cannot vibrate
so that actually,

01:08:07.420 --> 01:08:11.010
the boundary condition
at the closed end,

01:08:11.010 --> 01:08:17.279
where you have a wall closing
the tube, is psi equal to 0.

01:08:20.790 --> 01:08:25.370
And on the other hand,
if you have an open end--

01:08:25.370 --> 01:08:32.520
if you have an open end, that
means outside of the tube

01:08:32.520 --> 01:08:34.770
the pressure is equal to what?

01:08:34.770 --> 01:08:36.460
It's equal to P0.

01:08:36.460 --> 01:08:39.300
The room pressure.

01:08:39.300 --> 01:08:42.250
And you have so
many stuff there.

01:08:42.250 --> 01:08:46.260
Therefore, it's not
possible to actually change

01:08:46.260 --> 01:08:52.020
the pressure dramatically
at the edge of the open end.

01:08:52.020 --> 01:08:54.050
Therefore, what will
be the condition?

01:08:54.050 --> 01:08:59.910
Psi P. Psi P is again the
displacement with respect

01:08:59.910 --> 01:09:00.840
to the room.

01:09:00.840 --> 01:09:05.189
Pressure will be equal to 0.

01:09:05.189 --> 01:09:09.810
Based on what we
actually have learned

01:09:09.810 --> 01:09:16.060
from this expression-- sorry
for that, my finger slipped.

01:09:16.060 --> 01:09:24.410
From this expression, psi P is
equal to minus gamma P0 d psi

01:09:24.410 --> 01:09:32.800
dx So psi P is proportional
to partial psi partial x.

01:09:32.800 --> 01:09:38.240
Therefore, this
boundary condition

01:09:38.240 --> 01:09:45.000
actually translates to partial
psi partial x equal to 0.

01:09:47.609 --> 01:09:52.260
So this issue looks
really familiar to you,

01:09:52.260 --> 01:09:56.480
because in terms of psi, if
you forget about this system,

01:09:56.480 --> 01:09:59.940
what those boundary
conditions mean to you

01:09:59.940 --> 01:10:04.140
is exactly the same
as you have some kind

01:10:04.140 --> 01:10:09.450
of a wall in the left-hand side
and it's connected to a string,

01:10:09.450 --> 01:10:11.090
and the right-hand
side of the string

01:10:11.090 --> 01:10:15.030
is connected to a massless
ring which can actually

01:10:15.030 --> 01:10:17.140
move up and down.

01:10:17.140 --> 01:10:20.780
These two systems,
if you actually

01:10:20.780 --> 01:10:23.430
don't look at the detail--

01:10:23.430 --> 01:10:28.620
only look at the wave functions
and the boundary conditions--

01:10:28.620 --> 01:10:31.950
they are identical.

01:10:31.950 --> 01:10:35.250
So that's actually the first
lesson we learn from here.

01:10:35.250 --> 01:10:39.330
So when I talk about
sound wave or when

01:10:39.330 --> 01:10:41.910
you think about
sound wave problem,

01:10:41.910 --> 01:10:44.760
there's nothing to
be afraid of anymore,

01:10:44.760 --> 01:10:48.760
because that's actually the
same as what we have learned

01:10:48.760 --> 01:10:52.050
with wall and a string system.

01:10:52.050 --> 01:10:54.090
That's the first
thing we learned.

01:10:54.090 --> 01:11:00.660
Secondly, that only works
when I write my wave function

